tasks.solution:
### Broken version (to trigger red run)
```javascript
const { test } = require('node:test');
const assert = require('node:assert');

test('2 * 3 equals 6', () => {
  assert.strictEqual(2 * 3, 6);
});

test('this will fail', () => {
  assert.strictEqual(1 + 1, 3); // intentionally wrong
});
```

### Fixed version (to restore green run)
```javascript
const { test } = require('node:test');
const assert = require('node:assert');

test('2 * 3 equals 6', () => {
  assert.strictEqual(2 * 3, 6);
});

test('1 + 1 equals 2', () => {
  assert.strictEqual(1 + 1, 2); // corrected
});
```

### Sample observation summary
"The 'Test' step turned red within about 60 seconds of pushing. The Actions log showed exactly which assertion failed and what values were compared (expected 3, got 2). I knew precisely which test and which line was wrong without needing to search — the feedback was immediate and pinpointed to the single bad commit."

